                            <handNote>White letters against blue background. Letters in majuscule except υν in the word προστάτυν (line 6). Characters' size varies. Omega with crosslet, gama with a wavy horizontal bar, final sigma in ligature OC formed with a wavy, vertical line. Throughout the inscription there are many ligatures of the letters ΑΓ, ΑΡ, CT, ΟC, EI, ΤΡ, TH, ΗΡ, ΤΝ, ΝΜ, ΑΠ, ΟΥ, ΑΝ, ΤΟ, ΠΡ, ΝΗΜ, and ΔΗ. Tau is often positioned above omega and υν. Accents and breathings almost systematic. Breathings of the modern variety (circular).
