            <div type="translation">
                <p> Having been blessed in life with many good things
                    Of which thou, O Virgin, wast seen to be the 
                    provider,
                    I, Nikephoros magistros, a pitiable supplicant,
                    Erected this church with devotion,
                    In return for which I beg to fint thee my 
                    protectress
                    On the terrible day of judfement. (<bibl><ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>,<citedRange> 79</citedRange></bibl>)</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p> Very good condition. The inscriprion is made up of seven lines, which correspond to six verses. The sigla, which often mark the beginning and end of verses, are missing from this poem. The words βίῳ, χορηγός, ὡράθης, οἰκτρός, ἱκέτης, ἤγειρα, τόνδε, τόν, αἰτῶ, προστάτιν, εὑρηκέναι, τῇ as well φρικώδει are misspelled. Breathings and accents with errrors.</p>
            </div>
